==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Buckra
<hw>Buck"ra</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[In the language of
the Calabar coast, <ets>buckra</ets> means ⟦ldquo⟧demon, a powerful and
superior being.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>J. L. Wilson.</au>]</ety> <def>A white man;
-- a term used by negroes of the African coast, West Indies,
etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Buckra</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Buckra
<hw>Buck"ra</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>White; white man's; strong; good;
<as>as, <ex>buckra</ex> yam, a white yam</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Buckram</ent>⟦br⟧
